  <source>Fukushima Medical University</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The efficacy of anti-vascular endothelial growth factor (VEGF) therapy for branch retinal
      vein occlusion (BRVO) is shown, but its effect on retinal sensitivity is not fully
      investigated. The purpose of this study is to compare the changes in retinal sensitivity
      after ranibizumab therapy or combination therapy of ranibizumab and laser photocoagulation in
      eyes with BRVO.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
